1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 2=
(You Always Want What You Can't Get)

16
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,220
What's wrong with you today?

17
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:02,200
Why eat so little?

18
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:04,220
Does it taste bad
or do you have an upset stomach?

19
00:02:04,260 --> 00:02:04,820
No.

20
00:02:04,860 --> 00:02:06,990
I had some bread before evening study,

21
00:02:07,190 --> 00:02:08,420
so I'm not too hungry.

22
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,940
If you don't want to eat, forget it.

23
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,070
I'll put it away.

24
00:02:15,580 --> 00:02:16,860
Mom, let me put it away.

25
00:02:17,510 --> 00:02:18,020
Let me do it.

26
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:22,020
You're really sensible.

27
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:36,830
What are you doing?

28
00:02:36,860 --> 00:02:38,680
You're walking so slowly.
Hurry up. Walk.

29
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:45,140
Mr. Song.

30
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,560
Why did you
keep the lights off at night?

31
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,900
I just connected the lights
to electricity.

32
00:02:55,540 --> 00:02:57,500
What are you standing there for,
Chen Huan'er?

33
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,100
Come here.

34
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:02,350
Let me introduce you.

35
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,220
This is the puppy
from our compound.

36
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:05,200
It's called Xiaodi.

37
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:07,340
But not that you're here,
you're the new Xiaodi.

38
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:07,900
Sit.

39
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:29,740
What are you waiting for?

40
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:30,550
Eat.

41
00:03:32,270 --> 00:03:32,900
Let me tell you.

42
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:34,110
Aunt Hao

43
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:35,790
is the best cook in our compound.

44
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,620
Since I was little, I've looked forward
to my mom working overtime

45
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:40,940
so that she can send me
to their house for a free meal.

46
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:44,900
I'm

47
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:46,950
really sorry.

48
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:48,140
I'm troubling...

49
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:49,550
Don't mention it.

50
00:03:49,550 --> 00:03:50,460
Let me tell you.

51
00:03:50,510 --> 00:03:52,420
Mr. Song gave me extra food
because he saw

52
00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:53,860
how hard I trained.

53
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,040
Are you going to eat it?

54
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:57,110
I'll eat it if you don't.

55
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:59,700
What are you talking about?
Let her eat first.

56
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:00,990
Hurry.

57
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:02,140
Thank you.

58
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:09,990
It's good, right?

59
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:12,620
It's good.

60
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:13,350
I'll try it too.

61
00:04:14,510 --> 00:04:15,420
I'm telling you.

62
00:04:16,260 --> 00:04:18,670
We put a lot of effort
into this secret base.

63
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:21,710
None of the parents in this compound

64
00:04:22,150 --> 00:04:22,710
expected us

65
00:04:22,710 --> 00:04:24,710
to set up a blind spot

66
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:26,260
right along

67
00:04:26,550 --> 00:04:28,670
their daily commute route.

68
00:04:31,150 --> 00:04:31,740
Song Cong.

69
00:04:32,550 --> 00:04:33,150
Song Cong?

70
00:04:34,030 --> 00:04:35,710
Bring two more dishes to Huan'er.

71
00:04:40,150 --> 00:04:40,820
Coming.

72
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:01,420
Mom.

73
00:05:01,910 --> 00:05:04,030
Mom.

74
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:11,740
So is this where you saw me that day?

75
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,110
Yes.

76
00:05:13,910 --> 00:05:14,710
But rest assured.

77
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:15,670
I

78
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:17,110
won't tell anyone about it.

79
00:05:19,740 --> 00:05:21,990
I didn't cry that day.

80
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,740
I understand.

81
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:25,380
Girls

82
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:26,300
are self-conscious.

83
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:28,710
But don't worry.

84
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:30,300
Only heaven, earth, you, and I know

85
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,300
you cried

86
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:33,550
because of your exam.

87
00:05:33,550 --> 00:05:35,150
No third person will know about it.

88
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:35,820
Enough.

89
00:05:36,910 --> 00:05:38,550
Stop talking about Huan'er's crying.

90
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:41,150
No fourth person will know.

91
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:42,110
Rest assured.

92
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:43,820
Really.

93
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:46,350
I really didn't cry.

94
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:48,260
You didn't cry.

95
00:05:48,260 --> 00:05:49,230
She said she didn't cry.

96
00:05:49,230 --> 00:05:49,940
You don't believe?

97
00:05:49,940 --> 00:05:50,500
I believe you.

98
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,180
You didn't cry.

99
00:05:51,790 --> 00:05:52,620
Here, have a sip.

100
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,100
My mom's heavy-handed with seasoning.

101
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:54,700
Thank you.

102
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,470
There are so many dishes.

103
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:05,860
I can't finish it.

104
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:08,260
Don't mention it.

105
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:11,150
Everyone in this compound
knows each other.

106
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:12,860
Going to someone else's house for a meal

107
00:06:14,030 --> 00:06:15,860
is like our parents
working shifts at work.

108
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:18,880
Since you're here
at the family housing compound,

109
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:20,180
follow the organization.

110
00:06:20,590 --> 00:06:22,420
You should quickly adapt

111
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:23,180
and join us.

112
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:27,740
Next time when Aunt Lina is on duty,

113
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:29,150
come to my house for a meal.

114
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:32,230
If you refuse again,

115
00:06:32,230 --> 00:06:33,500
my mom will be angry.

116
00:06:39,180 --> 00:06:40,380
Fine.

117
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:43,420
I'll adapt

118
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,910
and try hard to keep up.

119
00:06:46,060 --> 00:06:47,470
If you need us in the future,

120
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:50,150
text us "Secret Base".

121
00:06:50,590 --> 00:06:51,180
And we'll know

122
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:52,820
you want to meet here in ten minutes.

123
00:06:53,910 --> 00:06:54,590
Okay.

124
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:57,620
Great.

125
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,420
We're finally a trio again.

126
00:06:59,420 --> 00:07:01,350
What do you mean you're a trio again?

127
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:02,710
Do you want to know?

128
00:07:04,260 --> 00:07:06,260
Lend me your homework for a week.

129
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:06,940
I'll tell you.

130
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:08,030
Don't keep me in suspense.

131
00:07:08,060 --> 00:07:08,940
Just tell me.

132
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:10,300
It's Li Tian.

133
00:07:12,110 --> 00:07:13,260
Li Tian?

134
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:15,180
Let's not talk about him.

135
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:15,820
Let's eat.

136
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:18,790
Go away.

137
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,420
Why didn't you bring it some food?

138
00:07:21,940 --> 00:07:23,380
It eats a lot every day.

139
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:24,260
Here.

140
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,230
Call it your senior.

141
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:27,260
I'm not its junior.

142
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,470
I'm the boss. It's your senior.

143
00:07:28,470 --> 00:07:29,230
Don't talk so much.

144
00:07:29,230 --> 00:07:30,990
Here, look at her. She's your junior.

145
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:31,760
Your new junior.

146
00:07:31,940 --> 00:07:32,420
Chen Huan'er

147
00:07:32,470 --> 00:07:33,550
is your new junior.

148
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,300
Does it need to be renamed?

149
00:07:35,350 --> 00:07:36,700
You don't acknowledge it anymore?

150
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,040
What shall we name it then?

151
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:39,020
Call it Second Senior.

152
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:39,880
You're junior.

153
00:07:55,790 --> 00:07:58,030
Song Cong, get up.

154
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:00,940
Huan'er.

155
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:03,150
I'm late.

156
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:04,120
I need to rush to work.

157
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:05,740
You hurry up.

158
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:07,380
Got it.

159
00:08:24,940 --> 00:08:25,670
Morning.

160
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,040
You didn't have breakfast, right?

161
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:29,230
My mom made it.

162
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,180
Is it for me?

163
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:34,350
Thank you.

164
00:08:41,990 --> 00:08:42,780
Cherish it.

165
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,460
It's my mom's turn tomorrow.

166
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:52,200
(Living in a family housing compound)

167
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,230
(finally showed an advantage.)

168
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:56,780
(You'll never go hungry.)

169
00:08:57,950 --> 00:09:00,140
(I'm not afraid
of how busy Mom is at the hospital.)

170
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,710
(The families will help each other.)

171
00:09:05,780 --> 00:09:07,430
(As for the cooking skills,)

172
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:10,380
(everyone is different.)

173
00:09:14,350 --> 00:09:15,350
Are you really eating it?

174
00:09:15,350 --> 00:09:16,620
I gave you and you really ate it!

175
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,360
What am I going to eat if you ate it?

176
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:20,780
Don't follow me.

177
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:31,070
(Our vegetable buns)

178
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:34,350
(still didn't receive
the family members' approval.)

179
00:09:34,430 --> 00:09:35,740
When is Aunt Hao's day off?

180
00:09:37,260 --> 00:09:38,660
If you don't like it, don't eat it.

181
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:43,060
(Tianhe No.1 Middle School)

182
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,190
I heard Song Cong
handed in his paper early that day

183
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,120
so that he could finish school
with Ms. Kao Sai.

184
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:48,860
Are they really...

185
00:09:49,070 --> 00:09:49,830
Stop talking.

186
00:10:03,260 --> 00:10:03,830
Huan'er.

187
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:07,070
Is there something going on
between you and Song Cong?

188
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,190
You believe it too?

189
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,620
But those who don't know
will believe it.

190
00:10:14,380 --> 00:10:15,740
Nothing is going on.

191
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:18,700
(Exercise Book)

192
00:10:27,980 --> 00:10:30,560
(Mathematics Questions)
Is it because of Song Cong's tutoring

193
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:32,520
that you made such great progress
in this exam?

194
00:10:37,820 --> 00:10:39,230
Can I take his tutorials together?

195
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,230
Sure.

196
00:10:41,470 --> 00:10:43,070
I'll talk to Song Cong.

197
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:45,500
Stand up.

198
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:50,070
Hello, Sir.

199
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:51,500
Hello, students.

200
00:10:51,909 --> 00:10:59,860
(Honorary Credential,
Song Cong Won First Prize)

201
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:05,950
Mr. Song.

202
00:11:06,350 --> 00:11:08,260
Are these leftover bottles
from infusions?

203
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:11,780
Empty saline bottles.

204
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:13,740
They're my dad's invention,

205
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,590
but I think

206
00:11:16,310 --> 00:11:17,350
it's no different

207
00:11:17,380 --> 00:11:18,590
than watering plants directly.

208
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:22,110
Mr. Song.

209
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:23,460
After we're done eating,

210
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,490
come to our house to play.

211
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:25,080
No.

212
00:11:25,470 --> 00:11:26,860
I have to tutor Huan'er later.

213
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:30,620
Tutoring on weekends?

214
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,640
I asked you to play football last week,

215
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:33,600
but you needed to tutor.

216
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:36,180
I asked you to go to the base before,
but you were also tutoring.

217
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:37,140
You too.

218
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:39,040
You come here for tutoring every week.

219
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:41,120
You even freeload meals.
Don't you think it's far?

220
00:11:41,950 --> 00:11:42,620
What's far?

221
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:43,920
We're all in the same compound.

222
00:11:43,940 --> 00:11:45,260
Huan'er, eat it while it's hot.

223
00:11:46,310 --> 00:11:47,190
Thank you.

224
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:48,470
As for you,

225
00:11:49,260 --> 00:11:50,020
I've never seen you

226
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:51,080
so proactive when studying.

227
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,450
When it comes to mealtime,
you're more punctual than others.

228
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,540
Aunt Hao, I went to play football.

229
00:11:55,540 --> 00:11:56,660
It's also a serious matter.

230
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:58,110
Your mother just told me today.

231
00:11:58,260 --> 00:11:59,590
Even if you're a special student,

232
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:01,230
you can't fall behind in your studies.

233
00:12:01,540 --> 00:12:02,470
I... Yes.

234
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:03,230
I'll stop talking.

235
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:04,540
I'll eat, alright?

236
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:05,350
Eat.

237
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:07,380
Aunt Hao, your cooking is delicious.

238
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:08,710
Much better than my mom's.

239
00:12:08,710 --> 00:12:09,500
Really?

240
00:12:09,710 --> 00:12:10,830
Eat more.

241
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:14,950
Chen Huan'er.

242
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:16,740
You're a bit unscrupulous now.

243
00:12:17,190 --> 00:12:18,470
I'll tell your mom later.

244
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:19,590
How dare you?

245
00:12:19,590 --> 00:12:20,310
Didn't you

246
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:21,400
flatter me before by saying

247
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,240
that my mom is the best cook
in the compound?

248
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:24,660
No. Why are you all

249
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:25,710
siding with her?

250
00:12:26,230 --> 00:12:26,740
Chen Huan'er.

251
00:12:27,060 --> 00:12:28,110
Let's do this one-on-one.

252
00:12:28,110 --> 00:12:29,160
Don't seek outside help.

253
00:12:29,430 --> 00:12:30,620
What one on one?

254
00:12:30,620 --> 00:12:32,260
Tell me properly.

255
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,230
Can you make it more international?

256
00:12:34,990 --> 00:12:36,110
Your English has improved.

257
00:12:36,110 --> 00:12:36,310
Yes.

258
00:12:36,310 --> 00:12:37,470
You're no longer Ms. Kao Sai?

259
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:38,190
Fine.

260
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:39,740
Let me drink some water to calm down.

261
00:12:40,430 --> 00:12:41,430
That's my water.

262
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:44,830
I know it's yours.

263
00:12:44,980 --> 00:12:46,380
Why did you drink it if you knew?

264
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:47,140
How delicate.

265
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:49,380
Everyone here shares their water.

266
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:51,440
What's wrong with drinking your water?

267
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:52,860
You have oil all over your hand.

268
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:53,620
Wash it.

269
00:12:53,780 --> 00:12:54,110
I won't.

270
00:12:54,110 --> 00:12:54,420
Wash it.

271
00:12:54,420 --> 00:12:55,780
Whoever drank first should wash it.

272
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:56,560
Didn't you drink it?

273
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:57,320
I won't washing it.

274
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,430
Why did you break the rules?

275
00:12:58,430 --> 00:12:58,780
Wash it.

276
00:12:58,800 --> 00:12:59,460
What's wrong?

277
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:01,100
I'm not washing it.

278
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,110
I'm not washing it today!

279
00:13:02,110 --> 00:13:02,620
Wash it.

280
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:03,080
Ouch.

281
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:03,680
Wash it or not?

282
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:04,190
Ouch.

283
00:13:04,190 --> 00:13:05,140
My arm hurts.

284
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:06,860
Mr. Song!

