So you don't need to go to the hospital

572
00:24:43,870 --> 00:24:44,870
if you have a headache.

573
00:24:44,870 --> 00:24:47,820
Knock on your neighbor's door,
and you'll get it treated.

574
00:24:48,670 --> 00:24:49,820
Yeah.

575
00:24:50,670 --> 00:24:51,950
But most importantly,

576
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:53,470
Phase 1 has good feng shui.

577
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:56,400
We all live
in the family housing compound,

578
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:57,950
but most of Phase 1's children

579
00:24:58,060 --> 00:25:00,190
have good grades.

580
00:25:00,390 --> 00:25:01,150
Really?

581
00:25:01,390 --> 00:25:02,820
The kid who used to live in your unit

582
00:25:03,020 --> 00:25:04,710
just got admitted
to Yenching University.

583
00:25:04,990 --> 00:25:06,020
Really?

584
00:25:07,340 --> 00:25:09,020
But there are also exceptions.

585
00:25:18,860 --> 00:25:20,670
By the way, we've eaten for a long time,

586
00:25:20,670 --> 00:25:22,190
why hasn't Dr. Li come back yet?

587
00:25:24,060 --> 00:25:26,060
The fathers in our compound

588
00:25:26,390 --> 00:25:27,670
are all the same.

589
00:25:27,950 --> 00:25:30,390
They usually don't bother
with the children's studies.

590
00:25:30,390 --> 00:25:32,470
They won't even come for a meal.

591
00:25:32,990 --> 00:25:35,230
But Dr. Li is really busy.

592
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:37,540
He has to take care
of all the big and small matters

593
00:25:37,540 --> 00:25:38,740
in the hospital.

594
00:25:38,740 --> 00:25:39,260
Yeah.

595
00:25:39,260 --> 00:25:40,500
I've said it before

596
00:25:40,780 --> 00:25:42,670
that he could just be

597
00:25:42,670 --> 00:25:44,950
the head of orthopedics department
like Mr. Song.

598
00:25:44,990 --> 00:25:46,060
He'll be free.

599
00:25:46,870 --> 00:25:49,470
How is he free?
He's having an operation right now.

600
00:25:51,430 --> 00:25:53,540
Where are Song Cong and Xichi?

601
00:25:54,630 --> 00:25:55,950
Xichi

602
00:25:55,990 --> 00:25:56,950
will be late.

603
00:25:57,230 --> 00:25:58,710
His class teacher is very responsible.

604
00:25:58,740 --> 00:26:00,740
Even asking him
to take extra lessons on weekends.

605
00:26:00,740 --> 00:26:01,390
That's good.

606
00:26:01,870 --> 00:26:02,500
(Extra lessons?)

607
00:26:03,990 --> 00:26:05,330
(He didn't go to extra classes.)

608
00:26:05,330 --> 00:26:07,120
(Zheng Lan Traditional Chinese Medicine Clinic)

609
00:26:07,470 --> 00:26:08,910
I already said

610
00:26:09,150 --> 00:26:11,630
that learning is the right way.

611
00:26:11,820 --> 00:26:13,430
After all, sports training is hard.

612
00:26:13,630 --> 00:26:14,580
Football, huh?

613
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:16,670
How many people succeed in the end?

614
00:26:17,740 --> 00:26:19,870
Xichi almost entered a sports school.

615
00:26:19,870 --> 00:26:21,870
He's also
the captain of the school team, right?

616
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:23,580
He's capable.

617
00:26:23,580 --> 00:26:24,470
That's right.

618
00:26:26,950 --> 00:26:27,910
What about Song Cong?

619
00:26:27,950 --> 00:26:29,740
I wanted to ask him

620
00:26:29,740 --> 00:26:32,230
to share his learning experience
with Tian.

621
00:26:32,230 --> 00:26:33,300
He's taking TOEFL classes.

622
00:26:33,470 --> 00:26:34,820
Starting this summer.

623
00:26:35,150 --> 00:26:37,190
After all, we agreed beforehand

624
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,790
that he'd only apply to
the top five universities in the world.

625
00:26:40,020 --> 00:26:40,870
Amazing.

626
00:26:41,990 --> 00:26:43,820
I'm full, so I'll go back to my room.

627
00:26:51,190 --> 00:26:51,910
Mom.

628
00:26:51,950 --> 00:26:52,990
I'm full too.

629
00:26:52,990 --> 00:26:53,740
I want to go home.

630
00:26:54,190 --> 00:26:55,990
Share your learning experience

631
00:26:55,990 --> 00:26:57,580
with Tian.

632
00:26:57,990 --> 00:26:58,390
Go.

633
00:26:58,390 --> 00:26:59,340
I shouldn't.

634
00:26:59,340 --> 00:26:59,910
Go.

635
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:01,540
Go.

636
00:27:01,780 --> 00:27:02,230
Go.

637
00:27:02,260 --> 00:27:02,870
Go talk to him.

638
00:27:02,870 --> 00:27:04,990
Mrs. Li, I'll go find Tian.

639
00:27:04,990 --> 00:27:06,860
I didn't expect
your daughter to be so amazing.

640
00:27:07,100 --> 00:27:08,430
I heard someone say

641
00:27:08,470 --> 00:27:10,190
that she won some award.

642
00:27:10,540 --> 00:27:12,020
Military boxing.

643
00:27:12,500 --> 00:27:14,630
Isn't Chen a martial arts coach?

644
00:27:15,260 --> 00:27:17,150
Mrs. Li, don't be scared.

645
00:27:17,150 --> 00:27:18,470
Huan'er

646
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:19,990
never bullies the weak.

647
00:27:19,990 --> 00:27:21,580
Really. She won't beat up Tian.

648
00:27:23,950 --> 00:27:24,670
Eat some food.

649
00:27:26,540 --> 00:27:27,300
Eat.

650
00:27:40,990 --> 00:27:42,910
Do you read books entirely in English?

651
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:44,710
Amazing.

652
00:27:44,710 --> 00:27:46,600
If you want to read,
take a book yourself.

653
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,230
If you have questions, find Song Cong.

654
00:27:48,340 --> 00:27:50,360
If you want to make friends,
find Jing Xichi.

655
00:27:55,670 --> 00:27:57,710
I know you don't like me.

656
00:27:57,710 --> 00:27:59,630
You don't have to worry
about what my mom said.

657
00:28:00,340 --> 00:28:02,740
Everyone will leave
after starting university.

658
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:04,580
There's no need to make friends

659
00:28:04,630 --> 00:28:06,080
and go through this process.

660
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:13,100
(IBT TOEFL Speaking Breakthrough)

661
00:28:14,430 --> 00:28:15,820
You want to go abroad too?

662
00:28:16,430 --> 00:28:17,820
Song Cong is also going abroad.

663
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:19,990
How come
you made up your mind in Senior One?

664
00:28:20,020 --> 00:28:21,020
I made up my mind first.

665
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,820
Besides, students
who enter Tianhe Middle School

666
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:29,800
have decided
what they want to do in the future.

667
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:31,460
Do you think
they're all the same as you?

668
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:32,980
If you're curious, ask Song Cong.

669
00:28:35,670 --> 00:28:36,260
Hello, Mrs. Li.

670
00:28:36,260 --> 00:28:36,990
Song Cong's here.

671
00:28:37,020 --> 00:28:38,060
I'm here to find Huan'er.

672
00:28:39,990 --> 00:28:40,630
Huan'er.

673
00:28:41,100 --> 00:28:41,910
Song Cong.

674
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:44,260
Didn't we agree to have a tutorial
this afternoon?

675
00:28:44,260 --> 00:28:44,900
Let's go.

676
00:28:45,910 --> 00:28:46,710
Yes.

677
00:28:47,430 --> 00:28:49,780
Well, let's talk again someday. Bye.

678
00:28:50,470 --> 00:28:51,300
Well, I've eaten.

679
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:52,630
I'll go tutor her first.

680
00:28:52,630 --> 00:28:53,540
We're leaving, Mrs. Li.

681
00:28:53,540 --> 00:28:54,780
Sure.

682
00:29:07,980 --> 00:29:12,540
(Certificate of Merit)

683
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:19,020
The problems you're looking at now are

684
00:29:19,020 --> 00:29:20,880
some of the more basic problems
we've learned.

685
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:22,500
Just apply the formula and solve them.

686
00:29:22,660 --> 00:29:24,280
But you have to memorize the formula.

687
00:29:25,470 --> 00:29:26,670
If you really can't remember,

688
00:29:26,710 --> 00:29:27,190
just look

689
00:29:27,190 --> 00:29:29,260
at the formula notes I compiled for you.

690
00:29:29,950 --> 00:29:30,540
Okay.

691
00:29:30,990 --> 00:29:32,060
Try solving it first.

692
00:29:32,260 --> 00:29:34,430
Why did you skip
your piano lesson today?

693
00:29:34,740 --> 00:29:36,080
I went to my classmate's house.

694
00:29:36,230 --> 00:29:37,150
I always reminded you

695
00:29:37,190 --> 00:29:38,580
not to associate with bad students.

696
00:29:38,780 --> 00:29:40,820
If you don't do well in this exam,

697
00:29:41,190 --> 00:29:42,740
I will change your tutor

698
00:29:43,100 --> 00:29:44,020
until you improve.

699
00:29:52,950 --> 00:29:53,950
Well.

700
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:56,100
I won't be able
to come for tutoring anymore.

701
00:29:59,910 --> 00:30:01,500
My mom is looking for a tutor for me.

702
00:30:03,820 --> 00:30:05,820
Qi Qi,
this is just your second time here.

703
00:30:05,910 --> 00:30:06,780
My...

704
00:30:07,430 --> 00:30:08,020
My mom

705
00:30:08,020 --> 00:30:09,300
is a little weird.

706
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:11,860
She previously wanted me
to go to an international class as well.

707
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:12,740
I asked her why.

708
00:30:12,950 --> 00:30:14,990
She said it's because it's expensive.

709
00:30:15,950 --> 00:30:17,060
Maybe she thinks

710
00:30:17,190 --> 00:30:19,230
it's only good if you spend money.

711
00:30:23,150 --> 00:30:25,630
It's normal for her

712
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:26,740
to have such ideas.

713
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:28,190
International class is good.

714
00:30:28,190 --> 00:30:30,320
You'll get good teachers
and you can study abroad.

715
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:32,990
Why is everyone going abroad?

716
00:30:33,780 --> 00:30:35,340
I saw Li Tian this morning.

717
00:30:35,420 --> 00:30:37,580
He also wants to take TOEFL
and go abroad.

718
00:30:38,230 --> 00:30:39,710
Li Tian's imitating Mr. Song.

719
00:30:39,710 --> 00:30:41,790
He failed the admission test
for international class.

720
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:43,080
He's upset.

721
00:30:44,390 --> 00:30:46,060
So you all already know

722
00:30:46,100 --> 00:30:47,990
what you're going to do
after graduation?

723
00:30:51,820 --> 00:30:52,870
I...

724
00:30:55,430 --> 00:30:56,500
want to be a writer.

725
00:31:01,230 --> 00:31:02,580
I want my children

726
00:31:02,580 --> 00:31:03,990
to see that the entire passage

727
00:31:04,340 --> 00:31:05,470
was written by their mom

728
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:07,600
when taking
a reading comprehension test.

729
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:10,910
That's

730
00:31:11,540 --> 00:31:12,990
a really vicious idea.

731
00:31:13,740 --> 00:31:14,580
What about Song Cong?

732
00:31:15,630 --> 00:31:16,630
What do you want to do?

733
00:31:21,260 --> 00:31:23,340
I haven't thought about it yet.

734
00:31:24,430 --> 00:31:25,340
Maybe

735
00:31:25,910 --> 00:31:27,780
I'll just do whatever I can.

736
00:31:28,040 --> 00:31:29,500
Look, you're doing it again.

737
00:31:29,540 --> 00:31:30,700
Why are you being humble?

738
00:31:30,740 --> 00:31:32,910
Aunt Hao already planned it for him.

739
00:31:32,910 --> 00:31:33,950
What plan?

740
00:31:33,950 --> 00:31:36,120
He's going abroad.
Is there any need to say more?

741
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:38,200
From participating in competitions
and winning awards

742
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,740
to applying to prestigious schools.

743
00:31:39,740 --> 00:31:40,780
He's different from us.

744
00:31:40,780 --> 00:31:42,020
He's going to do great things.

745
00:31:43,540 --> 00:31:45,630
It sounds so tiring.

746
00:31:46,820 --> 00:31:48,630
Will such a planned life

747
00:31:49,300 --> 00:31:50,340
make you happy?

748
00:31:57,670 --> 00:31:58,260
No.

749
00:32:00,020 --> 00:32:00,950
When I was young,

750
00:32:00,950 --> 00:32:03,180
my grandpa took me
to the mountains to dig herbs.

751
00:32:03,260 --> 00:32:04,120
He told me

752
00:32:04,150 --> 00:32:06,740
the most amazing thing about plants
is that they have no heart.

753
00:32:07,150 --> 00:32:09,470
Because
they have no feelings or emotions,

754
00:32:09,780 --> 00:32:12,060
they can survive
only by natural instincts.

755
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:13,780
But humans are different.

756
00:32:14,390 --> 00:32:17,670
Don't people live to be happy?

757
00:32:22,430 --> 00:32:23,580
Don't say so much.

758
00:32:23,580 --> 00:32:24,670
What is he unhappy about?

759
00:32:24,870 --> 00:32:26,630
He's a top student.

760
00:32:27,190 --> 00:32:28,190
Why are you so proud?

761
00:32:28,420 --> 00:32:29,440
Aren't you envious?

762
00:32:29,440 --> 00:32:30,420
Why should I be envious?

763
00:32:30,430 --> 00:32:31,500
I'm not Li Tian.

764
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,470
Besides,
do you think I'm an ordinary guy?

765
00:32:35,670 --> 00:32:37,260
If you want to see me in the future,

766
00:32:37,260 --> 00:32:39,580
you have to make an appointment
with my club, Real Madrid

767
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,470
six months in advance.

768
00:32:42,190 --> 00:32:43,630
Alright, hurry up.

769
00:32:43,630 --> 00:32:45,200
Or we won't be able to finish this.

770
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,140
You don't believe me?

771
00:32:47,100 --> 00:32:47,910
I believe you.

772
00:32:48,390 --> 00:32:49,060
Really?

773
00:32:49,060 --> 00:32:49,670
Really.

774
00:32:49,780 --> 00:32:51,300
Then say you believe me.

775
00:32:51,630 --> 00:32:52,910
I, Chen Huan'er, believe

776
00:32:52,910 --> 00:32:54,780
Jing Xichi will become
a professional player

777
00:32:54,820 --> 00:32:57,260
for Real Madrid in the future.

778
00:32:57,500 --> 00:32:58,150
You believe me?

779
00:32:58,150 --> 00:32:58,950
I do.

780
00:33:12,500 --> 00:33:14,190
I have piano lessons, so I have to go.

781
00:33:17,820 --> 00:33:19,470
Jing Xichi,
you don't need to see me off.

782
00:33:19,470 --> 00:33:20,260
I'm not.

783
00:33:20,630 --> 00:33:22,190
I'm going there too.

784
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,860
You want to learn
musical instruments too?

785
00:33:23,860 --> 00:33:24,780
No.

786
00:33:24,780 --> 00:33:27,180
I'm going to play football.
The football field is over there.

787
00:33:27,990 --> 00:33:28,780
Sure.

788
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:35,430
Qi Qi.

789
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:36,710
What do you think

790
00:33:36,710 --> 00:33:37,990
of what I just said?

791
00:33:38,630 --> 00:33:39,340
What is it?

792
00:33:39,630 --> 00:33:41,230
The one about me going to Real Madrid.

793
00:33:44,540 --> 00:33:45,620
You don't believe me?

794
00:33:46,100 --> 00:33:47,580
I happen to have a game next week.

795
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:49,160
Come and have a look if you have time.

796
00:33:49,430 --> 00:33:50,500
I think I'll skip it.

797
00:33:50,710 --> 00:33:52,190
I don't know much about these.

798
00:33:53,230 --> 00:33:54,580
It's good that you have a hobby,

799
00:33:54,580 --> 00:33:55,910
but our main duty is to study.

800
00:33:56,020 --> 00:33:57,620
We still have to get good grades.

801
00:33:57,960 --> 00:33:59,920
I'm leaving.
You don't have to see me off. Bye.

802
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:01,660
Come and have a look if you have time.

803
00:34:07,230 --> 00:34:08,910
(Song Cong and Jing Xichi...)

804
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:11,140
(One can't tell others his dream.)

805
00:34:11,870 --> 00:34:12,990
(The other one shared it)

806
00:34:13,500 --> 00:34:15,270
(but was dismissed as a childish fantasy.)

807
00:34:16,310 --> 00:34:19,140
(I don't know which is more frustrating.)

808
00:34:20,310 --> 00:34:22,310
(But I still envy them.)

809
00:34:23,180 --> 00:34:24,950
(At least they have goals.)

810
00:34:25,660 --> 00:34:28,950
(I don't even know where to go.)

811
00:34:30,540 --> 00:34:32,500
(I even used a small matter)

812
00:34:32,790 --> 00:34:33,750
(like untied shoelaces)

813
00:34:33,750 --> 00:34:35,180
(as an excuse to stay.)

814
00:34:43,430 --> 00:34:43,990
Mom.

815
00:34:44,580 --> 00:34:45,700
How come you're back so soon?

816
00:34:46,620 --> 00:34:48,620
Why didn't you
chat with Li Tian's mom longer?

817
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:51,360
Isn't the position that my dad
is being evaluated for this time

818
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:52,100
quite important?

819
00:34:53,220 --> 00:34:54,620
Let your dad worry about it himself.

820
00:34:55,180 --> 00:34:56,060
If I stay any longer,

821
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:57,540
I'll flip the table.

822
00:34:58,470 --> 00:35:00,350
You didn't see Li Tian's mom.

823
00:35:00,350 --> 00:35:02,190
When I told her
you were taking TOEFL classes,

824
00:35:02,220 --> 00:35:03,480
her face turned green with envy.

825
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:04,790
She's just jealous.

826
00:35:06,950 --> 00:35:09,060
I think you're a little too sensitive.

827
00:35:09,100 --> 00:35:09,470
Mom.

828
00:35:10,350 --> 00:35:11,390
I'm sensitive?

829
00:35:11,830 --> 00:35:12,270
Do you know

830
00:35:12,270 --> 00:35:13,620
how many years they've been talking

831
00:35:13,660 --> 00:35:14,830
about my low education level?

832
00:35:15,020 --> 00:35:16,140
What happened in the end?

833
00:35:16,350 --> 00:35:17,540
I still raised a child

834
00:35:17,540 --> 00:35:19,220
who's a top student.

835
00:35:21,310 --> 00:35:22,350
I also told them

836
00:35:22,660 --> 00:35:23,390
my son

837
00:35:23,660 --> 00:35:26,950
would only apply to
the top five universities in the world.

838
00:35:27,390 --> 00:35:28,470
Here. Have some walnuts.

839
00:35:29,830 --> 00:35:30,790
I have to thank you.

840
00:35:31,100 --> 00:35:32,830
You really make our family proud.

841
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:38,500
Mom, these walnut were given to you.

842
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:39,870
Eat them yourself.

843
00:35:39,870 --> 00:35:41,700
You usually think so hard at work.

844
00:35:42,470 --> 00:35:43,870
I'm not eating. You can eat them.

845
00:35:44,790 --> 00:35:45,870
You're my only child.

846
00:35:46,470 --> 00:35:48,020
You're our family's only hope.

847
00:35:48,580 --> 00:35:49,910
Eat more to supplement yourself.

848
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:56,060
I'll continue studying, Mom.

849
00:35:56,660 --> 00:35:57,700
Take these.

850
00:35:57,750 --> 00:35:58,870
Finish them. Here.

851
00:36:24,060 --> 00:36:25,830
(Will such a planned life)

852
00:36:27,790 --> 00:36:29,100
(make you happy?)

853
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:43,220
You're home.

854
00:36:43,660 --> 00:36:44,790
Mom, I'm home.

855
00:36:49,350 --> 00:36:49,910
Mom.

856
00:36:50,910 --> 00:36:51,910
Did you get a promotion

857
00:36:51,910 --> 00:36:53,020
or a pay raise?

858
00:36:53,140 --> 00:36:54,180
You spent so much money.

859
00:36:54,220 --> 00:36:55,910
That's why I said you're dumb.

860
00:36:56,100 --> 00:36:57,430
You're so oblivious.

861
00:36:57,470 --> 00:36:58,470
Look who's back.

862
00:37:03,100 --> 00:37:03,950
Dad!

863
00:37:04,220 --> 00:37:06,060
Dad!

864
00:37:06,060 --> 00:37:07,750
My girl.

865
00:37:11,140 --> 00:37:12,350
I missed you so much.

866
00:37:13,350 --> 00:37:14,990
Dad, what's going on?

867
00:37:15,020 --> 00:37:16,900
You betrayed me.
You didn't tell me in advance.

868
00:37:16,900 --> 00:37:18,350
I wanted to surprise you.

869
00:37:18,430 --> 00:37:20,500
Here, let me see
if you've grown stronger.

870
00:37:22,910 --> 00:37:24,100
Good job. You kid...

871
00:37:25,020 --> 00:37:26,020
Grappling hand?

872
00:37:26,020 --> 00:37:27,920
How many times have I told you
not to hurt her?

873
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:28,870
You think I'll hurt her?

874
00:37:28,950 --> 00:37:30,020
She'll hurt me.

875
00:37:30,540 --> 00:37:32,900
Good job. I can tell
you've been practicing a lot lately.

876
00:37:33,540 --> 00:37:34,620
But you guessed wrong.

877
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:36,340
I've been so busy with my studies lately

878
00:37:36,350 --> 00:37:37,750
that I don't have time to practice.

879
00:37:37,750 --> 00:37:40,100
How can you be so proficient
without any practice? Good job.

880
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:42,740
There are so many meat, Mom.

881
00:37:42,830 --> 00:37:44,100
You've worked hard.

882
00:37:44,620 --> 00:37:45,870
Dad, you don't you know.

883
00:37:45,900 --> 00:37:47,960
Mom rarely cooks this for me
when you're not around.

884
00:37:48,350 --> 00:37:49,100
How dare you

885
00:37:49,100 --> 00:37:49,870
complain?

886
00:37:49,990 --> 00:37:50,990
Look at this seafood.

887
00:37:51,020 --> 00:37:52,720
This shrimp.
I didn't even have this meat.

888
00:37:52,780 --> 00:37:53,870
Eat more.

889
00:37:54,750 --> 00:37:55,620
Eat more.

890
00:37:55,910 --> 00:37:57,100
I abused you.

891
00:37:57,660 --> 00:37:58,390
No.

892
00:37:58,500 --> 00:37:59,060
No.

893
00:38:00,390 --> 00:38:01,540
Come on. Hurry.

894
00:38:05,350 --> 00:38:06,700
The air today is really...

895
00:38:08,580 --> 00:38:08,790
Dad.

896
00:38:09,660 --> 00:38:10,270
Did you fart?

897
00:38:11,350 --> 00:38:12,540
Mom, he farted.

898
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:13,990
This smells like your mom.

899
00:38:13,990 --> 00:38:14,620
Cut it out.

900
00:38:14,830 --> 00:38:16,060
You ate too much corn.

901
00:38:18,870 --> 00:38:19,060
Dad.

902
00:38:19,470 --> 00:38:20,580
Since you're also here,

903
00:38:21,060 --> 00:38:22,750
what do you want me to do in the future?

904
00:38:24,220 --> 00:38:25,870
Jing Xichi and Song Cong's families

905
00:38:25,910 --> 00:38:27,270
already have plans for them.

906
00:38:27,420 --> 00:38:29,100
I'm sure you have one for me too, right?

907
00:38:30,220 --> 00:38:30,950
- No.
- No.

908
00:38:33,990 --> 00:38:34,660
Huan'er.

909
00:38:35,060 --> 00:38:36,900
Actually, you can do anything you want.

910
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:37,240
Yes.

911
00:38:37,260 --> 00:38:38,640
It's fine if you don't do anything.

912
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:39,190
That's right.

913
00:38:39,700 --> 00:38:40,950
How can that work?

914
00:38:41,350 --> 00:38:42,620
Dad, Mom, let me tell you.

915
00:38:42,750 --> 00:38:43,750
Our classmates

916
00:38:43,910 --> 00:38:44,790
are all

917
00:38:44,910 --> 00:38:47,140
ambitious and have goals.

918
00:38:47,350 --> 00:38:49,220
Although we come from a small place,

919
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:51,350
we must also have ambitions.

920
00:38:51,620 --> 00:38:52,310
Right?

921
00:38:54,140 --> 00:38:54,580
Ambitions?

922
00:38:58,950 --> 00:38:59,270
Huan'er.

923
00:38:59,270 --> 00:38:59,500
Dad.

924
00:39:00,910 --> 00:39:01,660
Actually,

925
00:39:01,990 --> 00:39:04,500
you have plenty of time to think.

926
00:39:04,580 --> 00:39:04,910
Yes.

927
00:39:05,270 --> 00:39:06,270
There's no rush.

928
00:39:06,700 --> 00:39:07,790
Take your time.

929
00:39:07,790 --> 00:39:08,750
Take one step at a time.

930
00:39:08,760 --> 00:39:09,320
That's right.

931
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:10,180
Got it, Mom.

932
00:39:10,580 --> 00:39:12,870
Aren't you talking
about the tortoise and the hare?

933
00:39:13,140 --> 00:39:14,310
I'm the tortoise.

934
00:39:14,390 --> 00:39:16,310
I'll win in the end, right?

935
00:39:16,310 --> 00:39:17,220
Girlie.

936
00:39:17,700 --> 00:39:19,580
- Life is not a competition.
- Yes.

937
00:39:19,700 --> 00:39:21,310
Why do you have to win or lose?

938
00:39:21,470 --> 00:39:23,310
It's okay if we don't win, right?

939
00:39:23,310 --> 00:39:23,660
Yes.

940
00:39:24,350 --> 00:39:25,500
We just hope

941
00:39:25,620 --> 00:39:27,270
you're healthy.

942
00:39:27,270 --> 00:39:27,660
Yes.

943
00:39:27,660 --> 00:39:29,700
Health and happiness
are the most important.

944
00:39:29,830 --> 00:39:30,750
That's right.

945
00:39:31,700 --> 00:39:33,100
Dad, Mom, actually...

946
00:39:33,100 --> 00:39:34,140
Enough talking.

947
00:39:34,270 --> 00:39:35,310
You don't get it.

948
00:39:35,700 --> 00:39:37,140
Children nowadays are so tired.

949
00:39:37,140 --> 00:39:38,060
Yeah.

950
00:39:38,100 --> 00:39:39,180
Why must there

951
00:39:39,180 --> 00:39:40,220
be a win or lose?

952
00:39:40,270 --> 00:39:42,020
It's not like how it used to be for us.

953
00:39:42,060 --> 00:39:43,700
You know, it used to be easy.

954
00:39:43,700 --> 00:39:45,830
Dad, Mom, your child's right here.

955
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:54,910
If you can kick this bottle

956
00:39:54,910 --> 00:39:56,100
with every kick,

957
00:39:56,420 --> 00:39:58,120
you will be close
to being a professional.

958
00:39:59,620 --> 00:39:59,950
Come on.

959
00:40:09,620 --> 00:40:10,750
You're not even close.

960
00:40:11,100 --> 00:40:11,430
Again.

961
00:40:12,100 --> 00:40:12,580
It's fine.

962
00:40:13,310 --> 00:40:14,500
It's only my first kick.

963
00:40:14,540 --> 00:40:15,880
If I kick it 10,000 times,

964
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:17,320
I'll definitely be able to kick it.

965
00:40:21,790 --> 00:40:22,060
Again.

966
00:40:24,940 --> 00:40:26,160
That's enough from you.

967
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:28,750
You're such a lousy player,
yet you want to play professionally.

968
00:40:28,790 --> 00:40:29,910
Just treat it as a hobby.

969
00:40:29,910 --> 00:40:30,430
No, Dad.

970
00:40:30,430 --> 00:40:31,180
Let me try again.

971
00:40:31,180 --> 00:40:32,260
I'll give it another try.

972
00:40:32,260 --> 00:40:32,750
Listen.

973
00:40:32,860 --> 00:40:34,420
Use your thigh to bring out your calf.

974
00:40:34,430 --> 00:40:35,620
This is where you exert force.

975
00:40:35,620 --> 00:40:36,180
Let me try.

976
00:40:37,700 --> 00:40:40,980
♪Wild roses in my hand♪

977
00:40:43,350 --> 00:40:43,910
Mr. Fu.

978
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:45,500
I want to change classes.

979
00:40:46,860 --> 00:40:48,420
♪From afar♪

980
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:50,000
I wondered why you're deliberately late

981
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:51,310
for the competition by 20 minutes.

982
00:40:51,310 --> 00:40:52,870
So it's to lay the groundwork.

983
00:40:53,310 --> 00:40:54,700
There was a traffic jam that day.

984
00:40:56,220 --> 00:40:57,870
And I won a place in the competition.

985
00:40:58,740 --> 00:41:01,100
I just hope you can agree
to let me change classes.

986
00:41:01,140 --> 00:41:03,020
Why do you have to change classes?

987
00:41:05,910 --> 00:41:06,830
I've made up my mind.

988
00:41:07,790 --> 00:41:08,580
I hope you'll agree.

989
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:12,660
Thank you, Mr. Fu.

990
00:41:15,180 --> 00:41:15,950
This kid...

991
00:41:36,921 --> 00:41:42,091
♪Fallen leaves flutter past your gaze♪

992
00:41:43,881 --> 00:41:48,961
♪I dream of worlds within your days♪

993
00:41:50,731 --> 00:41:56,081
♪Countless times,
I write your name in my heart♪

994
00:41:56,391 --> 00:42:01,881
♪Wishes whispered to the stars above♪

995
00:42:04,471 --> 00:42:09,491
♪How many faces in the glass I see♪

996
00:42:11,281 --> 00:42:16,521
♪Time's gentle hand
pulling me out of my cocoon♪

997
00:42:18,121 --> 00:42:23,541
♪Under the sun,
a rainbow butterfly takes flight♪

998
00:42:24,001 --> 00:42:29,501
♪To rest upon your left shoulder bright♪

999
00:42:30,701 --> 00:42:34,661
♪I still hear your promise in my ears♪

1000
00:42:34,661 --> 00:42:39,651
♪Before we said goodbye,
your spirit free♪

1001
00:42:39,781 --> 00:42:43,211
♪And full of life♪

1002
00:42:44,501 --> 00:42:47,961
♪If summer could last a little longer♪

1003
00:42:47,961 --> 00:42:53,071
♪Would regrets rewrite
where we'd gone wrong?♪

1004
00:42:53,331 --> 00:42:57,721
♪And let me be there with you
at the end of the story♪

1005
00:42:58,221 --> 00:43:02,121
♪Watching your silhouette from behind♪

1006
00:43:02,121 --> 00:43:07,061
♪My footsteps slow, we were too young♪

1007
00:43:07,061 --> 00:43:09,851
♪To know right from wrong♪

1008
00:43:11,761 --> 00:43:15,291
♪Your sweat-kissed face
I hold in my memory♪

1009
00:43:15,291 --> 00:43:18,541
♪Glows as bright as ever♪

1010
00:43:18,701 --> 00:43:24,461
♪I hope one day we'll meet again♪

1011
00:43:24,881 --> 00:43:29,481
♪At just the right time♪
